<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 5:51PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Union
and northeastern Claiborne Parishes through 615 PM CDT...
At 550 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cooley, or near Junction City, moving southwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Bernice, Cooley, Junction City, Lisbon, Spearsville, Lillie, Corney
Lake, Taylorville and Summerfield.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
